<para id="RM0000012GC00FX" category="J" type-id="300MW" name-id="ME0PP-01" from="200601">
<dtccode/>
<dtcname>Entire Combination Meter does not Operate</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM0000012GC00FX_04" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00009YK00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>This circuit is the power source circuit for the meter. This circuit provides two types of power sources; one is a constant power source mainly used as a backup power source, and the other is a power source mainly used for signal transmission. The constant power source is mainly used as a backup power source of the meter CPU, however, it is also used for communication. If a voltage of 12 V is not applied to terminal IG+ when turn the ignition switch on (IG), the indicator will not operate.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GC00FX_01" type-id="32" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00007RX00000">
<name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="E110182E09" width="7.106578999in" height="5.787629434in"/>
</figure>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GC00FX_02" type-id="51" category="05">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000012GC00FX_03" type-id="01" category="01">
